        "instructions": "1. Slice bitter melon then massage with salt. Set aside for 5-10 minutes. Rinse with cold water then drain.\n2. Chop garlic, shallots, and tomatoes. Slice the chicken in cubes.\n3. Sauté garlic, shallots, and tomatoes in a non-stick pan.\n4. Adjust the heat to high then add chicken. When the chicken is almost cooked, add a splash of water to prevent it from drying and clumping.\n5. Season with fish sauce and black pepper.\n6. Add the drained bitter melon and stir lightly. Cook for 2 minutes.\n7. Beat the eggs in a bowl then add to the pan. Mix lightly until the egg is cooked. Turn off the heat and serve."
